SSyynnooppssiiss
       cc [options] -Kthread file

       #include <pthread.h>

       int pthread_attr_setstacksize(pthread_attr_t *attr, size_t
       stacksize);      int       pthread_attr_getstacksize(const
       pthread_attr_t *attr,
           size_t *stacksize);

DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       pthread_attr_setstacksize   and  pthread_attr_getstacksize
       respectively, set and get the  thread  creation  stacksize
       attribute in the attr object.

       The stacksize attribute defines the minimum stack size (in
       bytes) allocated for the created threads stack.

RReettuurrnn vvaalluueess
       Upon successful completion, pthread_attr_setstacksize  and
       pthread_attr_getstacksize return a value of 0.  Otherwise,
       an error number is returned to indicate  the  error.   The
       pthread_attr_getstacksize  function  stores  the stacksize
       attribute value in stacksize if successful.

DDiiaaggnnoossttiiccss
       If the following condition is detected,  pthread_attr_set-
       stacksize  will  return the corresponding value: stacksize
       is less than PTHREAD_STACK_MIN or exceeds a system-imposed
       limit.    If   the   following   condition   is  detected,
       pthread_attr_setstacksize  and   pthread_attr_getstacksize
       will return the corresponding value: invalid attr argument

